#: admin/prayer-field-content.php:71
msgid ""
"God, we love you! As your Church, help us do what it takes to let the people "
"[of location] see you through Jesus, the radiance of your glory, the exact "
"imprint of your nature! (Hebrews 1:3)"
msgstr ""
"Dios, ¡te amamos! Como tu Iglesia, ayúdanos a hacer lo necesario para que la "
"gente [of location] te vea a través de Jesús, el resplandor de tu gloria, "
"¡la fiel imagen de lo que eres! (Hebreos 1:3)"

#: admin/prayer-field-content.php:72
msgid ""
"\"I am twenty-four and from Tunisia. I had a lot of debt and owed a lot of "
"people and the government money. I asked myself, \"Why don't I ask God to "
"help me?\" The truth is, I didn't ask because I didn't believe God would "
"help me. I left Islam and called myself an atheist. But, there was always "
"something inside me that said, \"There is a God.\" I began to search and "
"discuss with my friends. At that time, all of us were disillusioned, "
"searching for truth, and some had even become Christians. We all brought "
"information and shared with one another. Pray for us that we will discover "
"truth together.\"\n"
"\n"
"Pray for spiritual seekers [in location] and all over the Muslim world to "
"search and discuss the Bible with friends."
msgstr ""
"\"Tengo 24 años y soy de Tunisia. He le he debido dinero a mucha gente y al "
"gobierno. Me pregunté, '¿por qué no le pido a Dios que me ayude?' La verdad "
"es que no le pedí ayuda porque no creía Dios me iba a ayudar. Dejé el Islam "
"y me consideré ateo. Pero había algo dentro de mí que decía, 'Existe un "
"Dios.' Comencé a buscar y a discutir con mis amigos. En aquel entonces, "
"todos estábamos decepcionados, buscando la verdad, y algunos se habían hasta "
"convertido en Cristianos. Todos trajimos información y la compartimos entre "
"nosotros. Oren por nosotros para que descubramos la verdad juntos.\"\n"
"\n"
"Ora por buscadores espirituales [in location] y en todo el mundo Musulmán "
"que busquen y discutan acerca de la Biblia con sus amigos."

#: admin/prayer-field-content.php:75
msgid ""
"“When an attempt was made by both Gentiles and Jews, with their rulers, to "
"mistreat them and to stone them, they learned of it and fled to Lystra and "
"Derbe, cities of Lycaonia, and to the surrounding country, and there they "
"continued to preach the gospel.” (Acts 14:5-7).\n"
"\n"
"When attempts are made to mistreat believers [in location] - and even when "
"some must flee - may they be blessed with the boldness and perseverance to "
"continue to preach the gospel. (Acts 14:5-7) Lord, give them faith that "
"cannot be shaken by persecution.\""
msgstr ""
"\"Hubo un complot tanto de los gentiles como de los judíos, apoyados por sus "
"dirigentes, para maltratarlos y apedrearlos. Al darse cuenta de esto, los "
"apóstoles huyeron a Listra y a Derbe, ciudades de Licaonia, y a sus "
"alrededores, donde siguieron anunciando las buenas nuevas.\" (Hechos "
"14:5-7)\n"
"\n"
"Cuando hubieron atentados para maltratar a creyentes [in location] - y aún "
"algunos deben huir - que sean bendecidos con la valentía y perseverancia "
"para continuar predicando el evangelio. (Hechos 14:5-7) Señor, dales fe que "
"no puede ser sacudida por la persecución.\""

