#: admin/prayer-field-content.php:347
msgid ""
"Farah fled war-torn Syria with her husband and small children when the war "
"broke out. They found refuge in a nearby country and established a new life "
"together as a family. Although life was difficult as a refugee in a new "
"country, Farah discovered an openness she had not experienced in Syria. For "
"the first time, she could explore questions about faith and religion. In "
"April 2021, Farah messaged us through our Arabic ministry website. She "
"wanted to read the Bible but was unsure where to begin. Habib*, one of our "
"online Arabic responders, talked with Farah for several weeks. They chatted "
"online about many aspects of the Christian faith. Farah brought her "
"questions about the Bible to Habib, and they studied God's word together. "
"After a short time, Farah was convinced. She accepted Jesus Christ as her "
"savior and gave her heart to the Lord.\n"
"\n"
"Life did not get easier for Farah and her family. She faced persecution, "
"rejection and discrimination because of her new faith. She tried to share "
"the story of Jesus with her husband and children, but they didn't want to "
"hear about it. Undeterred, she began attending a local church and was "
"baptized. Farah continued studying the Bible, and her love for Jesus grew.\n"
"\n"
"She began meeting regularly with a group of Syrian women, and eventually, "
"she felt comfortable sharing her faith. They also wanted to know the peace "
"Farah felt, so each woman gave her life to Christ one by one. They now meet "
"in Farah's home and study the Bible together!\n"
"\n"
"Farah remains firm in her faith despite challenging circumstances, sickness, "
"pain, persecution and rejection. She is faithful and continues to pray for "
"her husband and children. Her love for Jesus has brought this precious group "
"of Syrian women to know and love the Lord. Praise God for Farah and her "
"brave desire to share her faith and be a witness to those around her.\n"
"\n"
"Now, because of Farah's* steadfast faith and determination, many others are "
"following Jesus.\n"
msgstr ""
"Farah huyó de la Siria devastada por la guerra con su esposo y sus hijos "
"pequeños cuando estalló la guerra. Encontraron refugio en un país cercano y "
"establecieron una nueva vida juntos como familia. Aunque la vida era difícil "
"como refugiada en un nuevo país, Farah descubrió una apertura que no había "
"experimentado en Siria. Por primera vez, pudo explorar preguntas sobre la fe "
"y la religión. En abril de 2021, Farah nos envió un mensaje a través del "
"sitio web de nuestro ministerio árabe. Quería leer la Biblia pero no sabía "
"por dónde empezar. Habib*, uno de nuestros respondedores árabes en línea, "
"habló con Farah durante varias semanas. Charlaron en línea sobre muchos "
"aspectos de la fe cristiana. Farah le llevó sus preguntas sobre la Biblia a "
"Habib y estudiaron juntos la palabra de Dios. Después de un corto tiempo, "
"Farah estaba convencida. Aceptó a Jesucristo como su salvador y entregó su "
"corazón al Señor.\n"
"\n"
"La vida no se volvió más fácil para Farah y su familia. Enfrentó "
"persecución, rechazo y discriminación a causa de su nueva fe. Trató de "
"compartir la historia de Jesús con su esposo e hijos, pero ellos no querían "
"saber nada al respecto. Sin inmutarse, comenzó a asistir a una iglesia local "
"y se bautizó. Farah continuó estudiando la Biblia y su amor por Jesús "
"creció.\n"
"\n"
"Comenzó a reunirse regularmente con un grupo de mujeres sirias y, "
"finalmente, se sintió cómoda compartiendo su fe. También querían conocer la "
"paz que sentía Farah, por lo que cada mujer entregó su vida a Cristo una por "
"una. ¡Ahora se reúnen en la casa de Farah y estudian la Biblia juntos!\n"
"\n"
"Farah se mantiene firme en su fe a pesar de las circunstancias difíciles, la "
"enfermedad, el dolor, la persecución y el rechazo. Ella es fiel y continúa "
"orando por su esposo e hijos. Su amor por Jesús ha llevado a este precioso "
"grupo de mujeres sirias a conocer y amar al Señor. Alabado sea Dios por "
"Farah y su valiente deseo de compartir su fe y ser un testimonio para "
"quienes la rodean.\n"
"\n"
"Ahora, gracias a la firme fe y determinación de Farah*, muchos otros siguen "
"a Jesús.\n"

#: admin/prayer-field-content.php:357
msgid ""
"“And they have conquered him by the blood of the Lamb and by the word of "
"their testimony, for they loved not their lives even unto "
"death.” (Revelation 12:11 ESV).\n"
"\n"
"Lord Jesus, by your blood your followers [in location] have become "
"conquerors of sin and death and even more than conquerors. May your church "
"[in location] cling to the eternal hope and promises that you have won and "
"may a heavenly host one day sing over them \"they loved not their lives even "
"unto death.\" (Revelation 12:11)."
msgstr ""
"\"Ellos lo han vencido por medio de la sangre del Cordero y por el mensaje "
"del cual dieron testimonio; no valoraron tanto su vida como para evitar la "
"muerte.\" (Apocalipsis 12:11 NVI)\n"
"\n"
"Señor Jesús, por tu sangre tus seguidores [in location] se han convertido en "
"vencedores del pecado y de la muerte y aún más que vencedores. Que tu "
"iglesia [in location] se aferre a la esperanza eterna y a las promesas de "
"que has ganado. Que sepan que un día un ejército celestial cantará sobre "
"ellos que \"no amaron sus vidas hasta la muerte\". (Apocalipsis 12:11)."

#: admin/prayer-field-content.php:361
msgid ""
"“It’s not that God has a mission for His Church in the world, but that God "
"has a Church for His mission in the world.” – Chris Wright"
msgstr ""
"\"No es que Dios tiene una misión para su Iglesia en el mundo, sino que Dios "
"tiene una Iglesia para su misión en el mundo.\" - Chris Wright"

#: admin/prayer-field-content.php:365
msgid ""
"God, we love you! As your Church help us do what it takes to let the people "
"[of location] grasp the Good News that Jesus offered a path to greatness in "
"the Kingdom that anyone could choose to follow! (Matthew 18:4)"
msgstr ""
"Dios, ¡te amamos! Como Iglesia tuya, ayúdanos a hacer lo necesario para que "
"la gente [of location] se aferre de las buenas nuevas de que Jesús ofreció "
"un camino hacia la grandeza en el Reino que cualquiera puede optar por "
"seguir. (Mateo 18:4)"

#: admin/prayer-field-content.php:366
msgid ""
"I am a forty-six years old woman from Tunisia. I saw a vision. The Messiah "
"said, “I am the Truth.” I had already given up on Islam because of the "
"violence. I never really felt God’s presence in my life before, but when I "
"saw the Messiah, everything changed. I felt God’s peace. I started reading "
"the Bible with some Christians.\n"
"                \n"
"Pray that our group of seekers will remain committed to knowing God through "
"His Word and obeying His commands."
msgstr ""
"Soy una mujer de Tunecina de 46 años. Tuve una visión. El Mesías dijo, \"Yo "
"soy la Verdad.\" Ya había abandonado al Islam por su violencia. Nunca había "
"sentido la presencia de Dios en mi vida, pero cuando vi al Mesías, todo "
"cambió. Sentí la paz de Dios. Comencé a leer la Biblia con algunos "
"Cristianos.\n"
"\n"
"Ora para que nuestro grupo de buscadores continue comprometido con conocer a "
"Dios a través de Su Palabra y la obediencia a Sus mandamientos."

#: admin/prayer-field-content.php:369
msgid ""
"“In days to come Jacob shall take root, Israel shall blossom and put forth "
"shoots and fill the whole world with fruit.” (Isaiah 27:6 ESV).\n"
"\n"
"Lord Jesus, would the hope of your glory and the joy of your salvation take "
"root deeply in your church [in location]. And by your grace and power, would "
"you cause spiritual fruit to blossom in this desert place, beginning a "
"joyful harvest of souls across the nations and the ends of earth, as you "
"have promised. (Isaiah 27:6)."
msgstr ""
"\"Días vendrán en que Jacob echará raíces, en que Israel retoñará y "
"florecerá, y llenará el mundo con sus frutos.\" (Isaías 27:6 NVI).\n"
"\n"
"Señor Jesús, que la esperanza de tu gloria y el gozo de tu salvación se "
"arraiguen profundamente en tu iglesia [in location]. Y por tu gracia y "
"poder, haz que mucho fruto espiritual florezca en este lugar desierto, "
"comenzando una gozosa cosecha de almas a través de las naciones y los "
"confines de la tierra, como has prometido. (Isaías 27:6)."

#: admin/prayer-field-content.php:373
msgid ""
"“Rediscover the real meaning of the Great Commission. Beginning in our own "
"prayer and devotional lives, we must begin to feel the compassion of the "
"Lord for a lost and dying world. As we have already seen, the Great "
"Commission is not something that was given to a tiny group of specially "
"trained and educated envoys. It was given to all Christians—to the whole "
"Church. It is something that we are all to be engaged in naturally every "
"day.” – K.P. Yohannan, Come, Let’s Reach the World"
msgstr ""
"“Redescubra el verdadero significado de la Gran Comisión. Comenzando con "
"nuestra propia vida de oración y devoción, debemos a sentir la compasión del "
"Señor por un mundo perdido y moribundo. Como ya hemos visto, la Gran "
"Comisión no es algo que se le dio a un pequeño grupo de enviados "
"especialmente capacitados y educados. Fue dada a todos los cristianos, a "
"toda la Iglesia. Es algo en lo que todos debemos participar naturalmente "
"todos los días”. – K. P. Yohannan, Ven, Alcancemos el Mundo"

#: admin/prayer-field-content.php:377
msgid ""
"God, we love you! As your Church, help us do what it takes to let the people "
"[of location] grasp the Good News that Jesus knowingly took one step after "
"another toward Jerusalem knowing He would be condemned to death, mocked, "
"flogged, crucified and then be raised on the third day! (Matthew 20:19)"
msgstr ""
"Dios, ¡te amamos! Como Iglesia tuya, ayúdanos a hacer lo necesario para que "
"la gente [of location] se aferre de las buenas nuevas de que conscientemente "
"dio un paso tras otro hacia Jerusalén sabiendo que Él sería condenado a "
"muerte, burlado, golpeado, crucificado y luego resucitado al tercer día. "
"(Mateo 20:19)"

#: admin/prayer-field-content.php:378
msgid ""
"Hamza is a 27 years old man who lives in Punjab. He has always lived his "
"life following Islamic rules closely but never felt satisfied as a follower. "
"He spent a lot of time looking at videos on YouTube and Facebook so he could "
"learn to do better but the more he looked the more he felt restless. One day "
"he was looking at Facebook and came across content about Jesus’ sacrifice. "
"He had never had an encounter with a Christian before and didn’t know much "
"about Christian faith. He decided to send a message and connected with a "
"believer. He told the believer that he tries to follow all the rules in "
"Islam but he always feels restless because he doesn’t have any hope he will "
"go to heaven. The Quran doesn’t tell him anything about having assurance "
"that if he keeps all the rules he will go to heaven. He asked many questions "
"about sacrifice, sacrificing animals and why Christians don’t perform any "
"sacrifices and came to the realization that Jesus is the only sacrifice he "
"needed. Hamza talked to the believer for about a week and decided his only "
"way to heaven is through Jesus. He put his faith in Jesus alone."
msgstr ""
"Hamza es un hombre de 27 años que vive en Punjab. Siempre ha vivido su vida "
"siguiendo de cerca las reglas islámicas, pero nunca se sintió satisfecho "
"como seguidor. Pasó mucho tiempo mirando videos en YouTube y Facebook para "
"poder aprender a hacerlo mejor, pero cuanto más miraba, más inquieto se "
"sentía. Un día estaba mirando Facebook y encontró contenido sobre el "
"sacrificio de Jesús. Nunca antes había tenido un encuentro con un cristiano "
"y no sabía mucho sobre la fe cristiana. Decidió enviar un mensaje y se "
"conectó con un creyente. Le dijo al creyente que trata de seguir todas las "
"reglas del Islam, pero que siempre se siente inquieto porque no tiene "
"ninguna esperanza de ir al cielo. El Corán no le dice nada acerca de tener "
"la seguridad de que si guarda todas las reglas irá al cielo. Hizo muchas "
"preguntas sobre el sacrificio, el sacrificio de animales y por qué los "
"cristianos no realizan ningún sacrificio y se dio cuenta de que Jesús es el "
"único sacrificio que necesitaba. Hamza habló con el creyente durante "
"aproximadamente una semana y decidió que su único camino al cielo es a "
"través de Jesús. Él puso su fe solo en Jesús."

#: admin/prayer-field-content.php:379
msgid ""
"“So also you have sorrow now, but I will see you again, and your hearts will "
"rejoice, and no one will take your joy from you.” (John 16:22 ESV).\n"
"\n"
"Lord Jesus, write the promise of your return and the power of your spirit "
"upon the hearts of your followers [in location] that they would be filled "
"with the joy of salvation and expectation that no one can take away from "
"them. (John 16:22) Even in the darkness of persecution and doubt and fear, "
"may their joy be unshakable."
msgstr ""
"\"Lo mismo les pasa a ustedes: Ahora están tristes, pero cuando vuelva a "
"verlos se alegrarán, y nadie les va a quitar esa alegría.\" (Juan 16:22 "
"NVI)\n"
"\n"
"Señor Jesús, escribe la promesa de tu regreso y el poder de tu espíritu en "
"los corazones de tus seguidores [in location] para que se llenen del gozo de "
"la salvación y de la alegría que nadie les puede quitar. (Juan 16:22) "
"Incluso en la oscuridad de la persecución, la duda y el temor, que su gozo "
"sea inquebrantable."

#: admin/prayer-field-content.php:383
msgid ""
"“Jesus promised his disciples three things: they would be completely "
"fearless, absurdly happy, and in constant trouble.” – G.K. Chesterton"
msgstr ""
"\"Jesús le prometió tres cosas a sus discípulos: ellos serían completamente "
"valientes, absurdamente felices y constantemente en problemas.\" - G.K. "
"Chesterton"

#: admin/prayer-field-content.php:387
msgid ""
"God, we love you! As your Church, help us do what it takes to let the people "
"[of location] grasp the Good News that Jesus taught that for God those who "
"have died are alive! (Matthew 22:32)"
msgstr ""
"Dios, ¡te amamos! Como Iglesia tuya, ayúdanos a hacer lo necesario para que "
"la gente [of location] se aferre de las buenas nuevas de que Jesús enseñó "
"que para Dios, aquellos que han muerto están vivos. (Mateo 22:32)"

#: admin/prayer-field-content.php:388
msgid ""
"Since I was child, I respected Islam, prayed, read the Koran and the Hadith, "
"and watched Islamic TV programs. As I prayed, I would cry out and ask God to "
"draw me closer to him. As I grew, I began to have problems with my family. "
"When I shared my opinion, it seemed like they just wanted to argue with me. "
"Finally, I left home to go and live with my sister. One night, as I cried "
"myself to sleep, I had a vision of a man. I could not see his face because "
"it was light. I could not stand and fell to the ground. In the dream, I was "
"young and small and was wearing a crown. He put his hand on me and said, "
"“You are mine. Don’t fear.” I tried to find an explanation for this dream. "
"Someone told me I had seen the Messiah. I didn’t know anything about "
"Christianity but began to search. One day I posted on Facebook,“My only hope "
"is that God will accept me.” A Christian wrote me and told me about God’s "
"love for me and sent me verses from the Bible. Inwardly I struggled between "
"what I had always believed and the new truth I was learning. I finally "
"decided to follow Jesus. I shared with my family and my brother, sister, and "
"niece also accepted Jesus.\n"
"                \n"
"Pray that we will start a church in our home and that we will boldly tell "
"others of God’s love."
msgstr ""
"Desde que era niño, respeté el Islam, recé, leí el Corán y el Hadith y vi "
"programas de televisión islámicos. Mientras oraba, clamaba y le pedía a Dios "
"que me acercara más a él. A medida que fui creciendo, comencé a tener "
"problemas con mi familia. Cuando compartí mi opinión, parecía que solo "
"querían discutir conmigo. Finalmente, me fui de casa para ir a vivir con mi "
"hermana. Una noche, mientras lloraba hasta quedarme dormido, tuve la visión "
"de un hombre. No podía ver su rostro porque estaba iluminado. No podía "
"pararme y caí al suelo. En el sueño, yo era joven y pequeño y llevaba una "
"corona. Puso su mano sobre mí y dijo: “Eres mía. No temas. Traté de "
"encontrar una explicación para este sueño. Alguien me dijo que había visto "
"al Mesías. No sabía nada sobre el cristianismo, pero comencé a buscar. Un "
"día publiqué en Facebook: “Mi única esperanza es que Dios me acepte”. Un "
"cristiano me escribió y me habló del amor de Dios por mí y me envió "
"versículos de la Biblia. Interiormente luché entre lo que siempre había "
"creído y la nueva verdad que estaba aprendiendo. Finalmente decidí seguir a "
"Jesús. Compartí con mi familia y mi hermano, hermana y sobrina también "
"aceptaron a Jesús.\n"
"                \n"
"Ore para que comencemos una iglesia en nuestro hogar y que con valentía "
"hablemos a otros del amor de Dios."

#: admin/prayer-field-content.php:391
msgid ""
"“and that repentance for the forgiveness of sins should be proclaimed in his "
"name to all nations, beginning from Jerusalem.” (Luke 24:47 ESV).\n"
"\n"
"Lord Jesus, impart your passion for your own glory among the nations to your "
"followers [in location] that they would be filled with wonder and "
"expectation at the seeming impossibility of seeing repentance for the "
"forgiveness of sins proclaimed in your name to all nations. (Luke 24:47) "
"Give your followers [in location] a burning passion for the great commission "
"and your global mission, even as they grow in boldness within their own "
"borders."
msgstr ""
"“y que se predicase en su nombre el arrepentimiento para el perdón de los "
"pecados en todas las naciones, comenzando desde Jerusalén”. (Lucas 24:47 "
"NVI).\n"
"\n"
"Señor Jesús, imparte tu pasión por tu propia gloria entre las naciones a tus "
"seguidores [en el lugar] para que se llenen de asombro y expectativa ante la "
"aparente imposibilidad de ver el arrepentimiento para el perdón de los "
"pecados proclamado en tu nombre a todas las naciones. (Lucas 24:47) Da a tus "
"seguidores [en el lugar] una pasión ardiente por la gran comisión y tu "
"misión global, incluso mientras crecen en audacia dentro de sus propias "
"fronteras."

#: admin/prayer-field-content.php:395
msgid "“Put legs to your prayers” – Ray Comfort"
msgstr "\"Ponle piernas a tus oraciones\" - Ray Comfort"

#: admin/prayer-field-content.php:399
msgid ""
"God, we love you! As your Church, help us do what it takes to let the people "
"[of location] grasp the Good News that Jesus invited us to make you the "
"center of our love and affection! (Matthew 22:37-40)"
msgstr ""
"Dios, ¡te amamos! Como Iglesia tuya, ayúdanos a hacer lo necesario para que "
"la gente [of location] se aferre de las buenas nuevas de que Jesús nos "
"invitó a hacerte el centro de nuestro amor y afecto. (Mateo 22:37-40)"

#: admin/prayer-field-content.php:400
msgid ""
"I am a married woman with two daughters. My daughters decided to follow "
"Jesus, and I fought with them about their decision for a long time. Over "
"time, I developed a liver disease. The doctor wanted to start treatment. My "
"daughters told me they would pray for me in the name of Jesus Christ. They "
"said, “He will heal you but more than that he will save you from your sins.” "
"I thought, “No problem. Let them try, and we will see what happens.” At that "
"time when they were praying, I was resting in my room alone and the weather "
"was very hot. I felt a gentle breeze blow over me. I heard a voice say my "
"name three times. Each time the voice was stronger. I got up and got "
"dressed. I went to my daughters and asked, “Did you call me?” They said, "
"“no.” They continued praying for me. Then I went back to my room and "
"realized that I had heard the voice of the Messiah, and He touched me by "
"healing me. The next day I went to the doctor. He said, “Please forgive us. "
"We were wrong. You are not sick.” I surrendered my life to the Lord and "
"began my journey walking with Him.\n"
"                \n"
"Pray for those who are sick and without hope. That Jesus will appear to them "
"and heal them so that they may know that He is true and is their Savior."
msgstr ""
"Soy una mujer casada con dos hijas. Mis hijas decidieron seguir a Jesús y "
"luché con ellas por su decisión durante mucho tiempo. Con el tiempo, "
"desarrollé una enfermedad hepática. El médico quería iniciar el tratamiento. "
"Mis hijas me dijeron que orarían por mí en el nombre de Jesucristo. Dijeron: "
"“Él te sanará, pero más que eso, te salvará de tus pecados”. Pensé: “No hay "
"problema. Que lo intenten y veremos qué pasa”. En ese momento cuando estaban "
"orando, yo estaba descansando solo en mi habitación y el clima estaba muy "
"caliente. Sentí una suave brisa soplar sobre mí. Escuché una voz decir mi "
"nombre tres veces. Cada vez la voz era más fuerte. Me levanté y me vestí. "
"Fui a mis hijas y les pregunté: \"¿Me llamaron?\" Ellos dijeron no.\" "
"Continuaron orando por mí. Entonces volví a mi habitación y me di cuenta de "
"que había oído la voz del Mesías, y Él me tocó al sanarme. Al día siguiente "
"fui al médico. Él dijo: “Por favor, perdónanos. Estuvimos equivocados. No "
"estas enfermo.\" Entregué mi vida al Señor y comencé mi camino caminando con "
"Él.\n"
"                \n"
"Oren por los que están enfermos y sin esperanza. Que Jesús se les aparezca y "
"los sane para que sepan que Él es verdadero y su Salvador."

#: admin/prayer-field-content.php:403
msgid ""
"“Though he slay me, I will hope in him; yet I will argue my ways to his "
"face.” (Job 13:15 ESV).\n"
"\n"
"Father God, grant your followers [in location] a profound trust in your "
"goodness and your sovereign power, that they might proclaim with Job "
"\"though he slay me, I will hope in him.\" (Job 13:15) Teach the church [in "
"location] to stand in awe and humble reverence toward your perfect plans and "
"purposes, even as the waves of tragedy and challenge wash over them."
msgstr ""
"\"He aquí, aunque él me matare, en él esperaré; No obstante, defenderé "
"delante de él mis caminos,\" (Job 13:15 RVR 1960)\n"
"\n"
"Padre Dios, concede a tus seguidores [in location] una confianza profunda en "
"tu bondad y en tu poder soberano, para que puedan proclamar como Job, "
"\"aunque él me mate, en él esperaré\". (Job 13:15) Enseña a la iglesia [in "
"location] a asombrarse y a tener una reverencia humilde hacia tus planes y "
"propósitos perfectos, incluso cuando las olas de la tragedia y desafíos los "
"inunden."

#: admin/prayer-field-content.php:407
msgid ""
"“I believe that in each generation God has called enough men and women to "
"evangelize all the yet unreached tribes of the earth. It is not God who does "
"not call. It is man who will not respond!” – Isobel Kuhn, 1901-1957, "
"missionary to China and Thailand"
msgstr ""
"\"Creo que en cada generación, Dios ha llamado a suficientes hombres y "
"mujeres a evangelizar a las aún no alcanzadas tribus de la tierra. No es "
"Dios que no llama. ¡Es el hombre que no responde!\" - Isobel Kuhn, "
"1091-1957, misionera a China y Tailandia"

#: admin/prayer-field-content.php:411
msgid ""
"God, we love you! As your Church help us do what it takes to let the people "
"[of location] grasp the Good News that Jesus is coming back like lightning! "
"(Matthew 24:27)"
msgstr ""
"Dios, ¡te amamos! Como Iglesia tuya, ayúdanos a hacer lo necesario para que "
"la gente [of location] se aferre de las buenas nuevas de que Jesús volverá "
"como un relámpago. (Mateo 24:27)"

#: admin/prayer-field-content.php:412
msgid ""
"I am a twenty-three year old woman. My family situation is very difficult, "
"especially with my father. I finally ran away. I went through some very hard "
"circumstances. One day a friend introduced me to a Christian family. They "
"welcomed me and told me about the Messiah. They said, “The Messiah is able "
"to help you in your suffering.” Later I got online and was looking for a "
"solution to my problems. Again, I was shocked to find information about the "
"Messiah. I met Christians and they prayed with me a lot. One day I woke up "
"and I had such joy in my heart. I heard a voice say, “Accept the Messiah. "
"Accept the Messiah.” I accepted Christ and was filled with the Holy Spirit. "
"I felt new life come into my body and fill me with strength and renew my "
"soul. Within a week, God began to prompt me to forgive my father. Pray that "
"God will give me faith to trust Him and forgive my father. Pray for others "
"who are bound by the slavery of bitterness and unforgiveness.\n"
"                \n"
"Pray that God will give them strength to forgive."
msgstr ""
"Soy una mujer de veintitrés años. Mi situación familiar es muy difícil, "
"especialmente con mi padre. Finalmente me escapé. Pasé por circunstancias "
"muy duras. Un día un amigo me presentó a una familia cristiana. Me "
"recibieron y me hablaron del Mesías. Dijeron: \"El Mesías puede ayudarte en "
"tu sufrimiento\". Más tarde me conecté y estaba buscando una solución a mis "
"problemas. Una vez más, me sorprendió encontrar información sobre el Mesías. "
"Conocí cristianos y oraron mucho conmigo. Un día me desperté y tenía tanta "
"alegría en mi corazón. Escuché una voz que decía: “Acepta al Mesías. Acepta "
"al Mesías”. Acepté a Cristo y fui lleno del Espíritu Santo. Sentí que una "
"nueva vida entraba en mi cuerpo y me llenaba de fuerzas y renovaba mi alma. "
"En una semana, Dios comenzó a incitarme a perdonar a mi padre. Ore para que "
"Dios me dé fe para confiar en Él y perdonar a mi padre. Ore por otros que "
"están atados por la esclavitud de la amargura y la falta de perdón.\n"
"                \n"
"Ore para que Dios les dé fuerza para perdonar."

#: admin/prayer-field-content.php:415
msgid ""
"“Go your way; behold, I am sending you out as lambs in the midst of "
"wolves.” (Luke 10:3 ESV).\n"
"\n"
"Lord Jesus, you have sent your followers [in location] out as lambs in the "
"midst of wolves. Be their ever-mindful, every-caring shepherd as you grow "
"them in confidence and steadfastness to trust you as the wolves encircle and "
"threaten. Would you give them a supernatural, attractive gentleness that "
"even their suffering might a witness to their enemies who would see them "
"divided and lost. (Luke 10:3)."
msgstr ""
"\"¡Vayan ustedes! Miren que los envío como corderos en medio de lobos."
"\" (Lucas 10:3 NVI)\n"
"\n"
"Señor Jesús, has enviado a tus seguidores [in location] como a corderos en "
"medio de lobos. Se tú su pastor siempre consciente y siempre atento. Haz "
"crecer su confianza y firmeza para confiar en ti en medio de los lobos que "
"los rodean y amenazan. Dales, Señor, una dulzura sobrenatural y atractiva "
"para que incluso su sufrimiento pudiera ser un testimonio para sus enemigos "
"que desean verlos divididos y perdidos. (Lucas 10:3)."

#: admin/prayer-field-content.php:419
msgid ""
"“If you are ever inclined to pray for a missionary, do it at once, where "
"ever you are. Perhaps he may be in great peril at that moment.” – Amy "
"Carmichael, 1867-1951, missionary to India"
msgstr ""
"\"Si eres conmovido a orar por un misionero, hazlo en ese mismo instante, "
"estés donde estés. Puede que esté en gran peligro justo en ese momento.\" - "
"Amy Carmichael, 1867 - 1951, misionera a la India"

#: admin/prayer-field-content.php:423
msgid ""
"God, we love you! As your Church, help us do what it takes to let the people "
"[of location] grasp the Good News that Jesus will bless those who are "
"faithful in this life! (Matthew 24:47)"
msgstr ""
"Dios, ¡te amamos! Como Iglesia tuya, ayúdanos a hacer lo necesario para que "
"la gente [of location] se aferre de las buenas nuevas de que Jesús bendecirá "
"a aquellos que son fieles en esta vida. (Mateo 24:47)"

#: admin/prayer-field-content.php:424
msgid ""
"I am Nasser, and I am from Afghanistan. When I was a teenager, my family "
"fled The Taliban and went to Pakistan. I was from a well-to-do family, and "
"my parents had money to send my siblings and I to learn English at a "
"learning center there that some westerners taught at. One of the teachers "
"played the guitar really well, and I hadn't heard this instrument before - "
"we have other kinds of instruments in Afghanistan. I asked him if he would "
"come home with me to play the guitar at my house and have dinner with my "
"family. Before beginning dinner, my father thought to honor our guest and "
"his culture by asking him to thank Allah for the food. As the westerner "
"prayed, it was the first time I felt peace in my entire tumultuous life -- I "
"looked at this man as he prayed, and I could see this overwhelming peace and "
"joy, and I wanted it. As he finished praying, I heard him say in Urdu, \"in "
"Jesus' name, Amen.\" I knew then there must be some connection to Jesus and "
"this guy's peace and joy. In the coming weeks, that man led me to Christ, "
"and then I led my family to Christ. We moved back to Afghanistan a couple "
"years later, and by the grace of God we saw many Afghans come to faith in "
"Christ, some even who are still in Afghanistan and remain a light under the "
"current regime.\n"
"\n"
"Please pray for the persecuted church in Afghanistan:\n"
"- to love their enemies\n"
"- to be filled with love and boldness to share the gospel, heal the sick and "
"cast out demons\n"
"- to multiply disciples, churches, and leaders among every people and place "
"in that country"
msgstr ""
"Soy Nasser y soy de Afganistán. Cuando era adolescente, mi familia huyó de "
"los talibanes y se fue a Pakistán. Yo era de una familia acomodada, y mis "
"padres tenían dinero para enviarnos a mis hermanos y a mí a aprender inglés "
"en un centro de aprendizaje en el que enseñaban algunos occidentales. Uno de "
"los profesores tocaba muy bien la guitarra y yo no había oído este "
"instrumento antes. Tenemos otros tipos de instrumentos en Afganistán. Le "
"pregunté si vendría a casa conmigo para tocar la guitarra en mi casa y cenar "
"con mi familia. Antes de comenzar la cena, mi padre pensó en honrar a "
"nuestro invitado y su cultura pidiéndole que agradeciera a Allah por la "
"comida. Mientras oraba el occidental, fue la primera vez que sentí paz en "
"toda mi tumultuosa vida. Miré a este hombre mientras oraba y pude ver esta "
"paz y alegría abrumadoras, y lo deseaba. Cuando terminó de orar, lo escuché "
"decir en urdu, \"en el nombre de Jesús, amén\". Entonces supe que debía "
"haber alguna conexión con Jesús y la paz y el gozo de este hombre. En las "
"próximas semanas, ese hombre me guió a Cristo, y luego guié a mi familia a "
"Cristo. Regresamos a Afganistán un par de años después y, por la gracia de "
"Dios, vimos a muchos afganos llegar a la fe en Cristo, algunos incluso que "
"todavía están en Afganistán y siguen siendo una luz bajo el régimen actual.\n"
"\n"
"Por favor oren por la iglesia perseguida en Afganistán:\n"
"- amar a sus enemigos\n"
"- estar llenos de amor y audacia para compartir el evangelio, sanar a los "
"enfermos y expulsar demonios\n"
"- multiplicar discípulos, iglesias y líderes entre cada pueblo y lugar en "
"ese país"

#: admin/prayer-field-content.php:430
msgid ""
"“in whom we have boldness and access with confidence through our faith in "
"him.” (Ephesians 3:12 ESV).\n"
"\n"
"Lord God, grant your followers [in location] the boldness and confidence "
"reserved for Sons and Daughters of the King as you reassure them not only of "
"their salvation, but their commissioning as witnesses and ministers in this "
"broken world. (Ephesians 3:12) Remove by your gentle spirit any lie or "
"obstacle that would threaten the confidence with which these precious ones "
"enter the Holy of Holies."
msgstr ""
"\"En él, mediante la fe, disfrutamos de libertad y confianza para acercarnos "
"a Dios.\" (Efesios 3:12 NVI).\n"
"\n"
"Señor Dios, concédele a tus seguidores [in location] la audacia y confianza "
"reservada para los hijos e hijas del Rey ya que tú le reafirmas a ellos no "
"sólo su salvación pero su comisión como testigos y ministros en este mundo "
"quebrado. (Efesios 3:12) Remueve por tu gentil espíritu cualquier mentira u "
"obstáculo que pudiera amenazar la confianza con la cual estos preciosos "
"hijos tuyos entran al Lugar Santísimo."

#: admin/prayer-field-content.php:434
msgid ""
"“Prayer is not a preparation for the battle; it is the battle!” – Leonard "
"Ravenhill"
msgstr ""
"\"La oración no es una preparación para la batalla; ¡es la batalla!\" - "
"Leonard Ravenhill"

#: admin/prayer-field-content.php:438
msgid ""
"God, we love you! As your Church, help us do what it takes to let the people "
"[of location] grasp the Good News that Jesus eagerly awaits the Kingdom to "
"drink wine with us! (Matthew 26:29)"
msgstr ""
"Dios, ¡te amamos! Como Iglesia tuya, ayúdanos a hacer lo necesario para que "
"la gente [of location] se aferre de las buenas nuevas de que Jesús aguarda "
"con ansias al Reino para beber vino con nosotros. (Mateo 26:29)"

#: admin/prayer-field-content.php:439
msgid ""
"I am a thirty-year-old man from Tunisia. I was raised in a strict, "
"practicing Muslim family. The first time I went to a church building, I had "
"a government job to watch the Christians. I was surprised by their simple "
"message and wondered why we were afraid of them. One day the Christians gave "
"me a Bible and explained it to me. They prayed for me. I went home and "
"prayed, “God, you know me. If you are true, speak to me.” I had a dream. "
"There were six people being crucified on a cross. The Messiah was also on a "
"cross. My friend from the police gave me a gun and said to shoot them. The "
"Messiah said, “I will never die,” and then he pointed to the others, “They "
"will not die either.” I woke up and called my friend in the dream. He had "
"had the same dream! I understand that only the Messiah offers eternal life "
"and that is why Christians are not afraid. I gave my life to Christ.\n"
"                \n"
"Pray that Muslims this Ramadan will have dreams of Christ and will not be "
"afraid to share the Good News!"
msgstr ""
"Soy un hombre de treinta años de Túnez. Me crié en una familia musulmana "
"estricta y practicante. La primera vez que fui al edificio de una iglesia, "
"tenía un trabajo en el gobierno para vigilar a los cristianos. Me sorprendió "
"su mensaje simple y me pregunté por qué les teníamos miedo. Un día los "
"cristianos me dieron una Biblia y me la explicaron. Rezaron por mí. Fui a "
"casa y oré: “Dios, tú me conoces. Si eres sincero, háblame. Tuve un sueño. "
"Había seis personas siendo crucificadas en una cruz. El Mesías también "
"estaba en una cruz. Mi amigo de la policía me dio un arma y me dijo que les "
"disparara. El Mesías dijo: “Yo nunca moriré”, y luego señaló a los demás: "
"“Ellos tampoco morirán”. Me desperté y llamé a mi amigo en el sueño. ¡Él "
"había tenido el mismo sueño! Entiendo que sólo el Mesías ofrece la vida "
"eterna y por eso los cristianos no tienen miedo. Le di mi vida a Cristo.\n"
"                \n"
"¡Ore para que los musulmanes este Ramadán tengan sueños de Cristo y no "
"tengan miedo de compartir las Buenas Nuevas!"

#: admin/prayer-field-content.php:442
msgid ""
"“But though we had already suffered and been shamefully treated at Philippi, "
"as you know, we had boldness in our God to declare to you the gospel of God "
"in the midst of much conflict.” (1 Thessalonians 2:2 ESV).\n"
"\n"
"Lord Jesus, you see the shameful treatment and suffering of many of your "
"followers [in location]. And we pray that as your sovereign hand guides them "
"through adversity, they would rise up in boldness in their God to continue "
"to declare the gospel in the midst of much conflict. (1 Thessalonians 2:2) "
"May there be no conflict or persecution that quiets the voices of your "
"church [in location]."
msgstr ""
"“Pero aunque ya habíamos padecido y sido afrentados en Filipos, como sabéis, "
"tuvimos confianza en nuestro Dios para anunciaros el evangelio de Dios en "
"medio de mucho conflicto.” (1 Tesalonicenses 2:2 NVI).\n"
"\n"
"Señor Jesús, ves el trato vergonzoso y el sufrimiento de muchos de tus "
"seguidores [en el lugar]. Y oramos para que a medida que tu mano soberana "
"los guíe a través de la adversidad, se levanten con denuedo en su Dios para "
"continuar declarando el evangelio en medio de mucho conflicto. (1 "
"Tesalonicenses 2:2) Que no haya conflicto ni persecución que acalle las "
"voces de vuestra iglesia [in location]."

#: admin/prayer-field-content.php:446
msgid ""
"“We never know how God will answer our prayers, but we can expect that He "
"will get us involved in His plan for the answer. If we are true "
"intercessors, we must be ready to take part in God’s work on behalf of the "
"people for whom we pray.” – Corrie Ten Boom"
msgstr ""
"\"Nunca sabremos cómo Dios responderá a nuestras oraciones, pero podemos "
"esperar que Él nos involucrará en Su plan para la respuesta. Si somos "
"verdaderos intercesores, debemos estar listos para ser parte del trabajo de "
"Dios en nombre de las personas por quienes oramos.\" - Corrie Ten Boom"

#: admin/prayer-field-content.php:450
msgid ""
"God, we love you! As your Church, help us do what it takes to let the people "
"[of location] grasp the Good News that Jesus will be seated at the right "
"hand of Power and come on the clouds of Heaven! (Matthew 26:64)"
msgstr ""
"Dios, ¡te amamos! Como Iglesia tuya, ayúdanos a hacer lo necesario para que "
"la gente [of location] se aferre de las buenas nuevas de que Jesús estará "
"sentado a la derecha del Todopoderoso, y viniendo en las nubes del cielo. "
"(Mateo 26:64)"

#: admin/prayer-field-content.php:451
msgid ""
"I am a twenty-two year old woman and study at the university. Before I was "
"born, my mother dedicated me to an Islamic saint and made a covenant. Every "
"year of my life I was made to go back to where the Islamic saint is buried, "
"cut myself, and do a blood sacrifice. I feel that I have been in spiritual "
"bondage and want to break free. I had a vision six times in which someone "
"was holding my hand. The man said, “I love you. Follow me.” I wondered if He "
"could be the Messiah. I searched in many places. Finally, I found someone on "
"the internet who explained God’s love to me. Unfortunately, I have been "
"living in much sin and all of my friends are like me. At first, I was in "
"denial that my actions were actually sin, but the Lord convicted me and I "
"spent one night in a prayer of repentance. I know of many others, like me, "
"living in sin.\n"
"            \n"
"            Please pray that God will convict them of their sins, rescue "
"them, and give them new life. Pray also that I will be completely free in "
"Christ."
msgstr ""
"Soy una mujer de veintidós años y estudio en la universidad. Antes de nacer, "
"mi madre me dedicó a un santo islámico e hizo un pacto. Cada año de mi vida "
"me obligaron a volver al lugar donde está enterrado el santo islámico, "
"cortarme y hacer un sacrificio de sangre. Siento que he estado en cautiverio "
"espiritual y quiero liberarme. Tuve una visión seis veces en la que alguien "
"me tomaba la mano. El hombre dijo: “Te amo. Sígueme.\" Me preguntaba si Él "
"podría ser el Mesías. Busqué en muchos lugares. Finalmente, encontré a "
"alguien en Internet que me explicó el amor de Dios. Desafortunadamente, he "
"estado viviendo en mucho pecado y todos mis amigos son como yo. Al "
"principio, estaba en negación de que mis acciones fueran en realidad pecado, "
"pero el Señor me convenció y pasé una noche en una oración de penitencia. Sé "
"de muchos otros, como yo, que viven en pecado.\n"
"            \n"
"            Por favor, oren para que Dios los convenza de sus pecados, los "
"rescate y les dé nueva vida. Oren también para que sea completamente libre "
"en Cristo."

#: admin/prayer-field-content.php:454
msgid ""
"“And he put the wood in order and cut the bull in pieces and laid it on the "
"wood. And he said, “Fill four jars with water and pour it on the burnt "
"offering and on the wood.”” (1 Kings 18:33 ESV).\n"
"\n"
"Lord God, give your church [in location] the boldness of Elijah who called "
"for more water to soak the burnt offering before the eyes of the watching "
"world. Grant that same spirit to your followers [in location] that they "
"might boldly call upon your power and name to deliver and to witness to your "
"majesty before the watchful eyes [of location] and all the nations of the "
"earth. (1 Kings 18:33)."
msgstr ""
"“Y puso la leña en orden y cortó el toro en pedazos y lo puso sobre la leña. "
"Y él dijo: “Llenad cuatro cántaros de agua y derramáis sobre el holocausto y "
"sobre la leña.”” (1 Reyes 18:33 NVI).\n"
"\n"
"Señor Dios, da a tu iglesia [in location] la audacia de Elías que pidió más "
"agua para remojar el holocausto ante los ojos del mundo que miraba. Otorga "
"ese mismo espíritu a tus seguidores [in location] para que audazmente "
"invoquen tu poder y nombre para liberar y dar testimonio de tu majestad ante "
"los ojos vigilantes [of location] y de todas las naciones de la tierra. (1 "
"Reyes 18:33)."

